\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Dominant representation costs of the solver methods. Here $n$ is total sample size, $p$ is feature count, $p_{\mathrm  {eff}}$ is the number of coordinates included in the L2 fusion block, $k$ is group count, $m=|E|$ is the number of active fusion edges, and $q=\binom  {k}{2}$. The table isolates graph-representation costs and omits lower-order constants from solver overhead.}}{16}{table.2}\protected@file@percent }
